  <brief_title>Prone Versus Left-sided Colonoscopy in Obese Patients</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Dallas VA Medical Center</agency>
      <agency_class>U.S. Fed</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Dallas VA Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      For obese patients, a randomized trial aimed at determining whether colonoscopy performance
      and patient comfort is improved if a patient is in the prone position (lay on their abdomen)
      versus the traditional left-sided position.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
